# Riverpod 3 + Clean Architecture

This project uses three layers: `data`, `domain`, `presentation`.

## Layer boundaries

- Keep entities, enums, and repository contracts in `lib/domain`.
- Keep Firebase and other external implementations in `lib/data`.
- Keep widgets, pages, and providers in `lib/presentation`.
- `presentation` may depend on `domain` contracts and `presentation/providers`.
- `data` may depend on `domain`, but `domain` must not depend on `data` or `presentation`.
- Do not add a new architectural layer (for example `usecases`) unless explicitly requested.

## Riverpod 3 conventions

- Use `ProviderScope` at app root.
- Prefer `AsyncNotifier` + `AsyncNotifierProvider` for async feature state.
- Keep repository injection inside providers, reading domain repository interfaces.
- Keep provider names explicit and feature-scoped (`<feature>NotifierProvider`, `<feature>RepositoryProvider`).
- Handle loading and errors with `AsyncValue` states instead of ad-hoc booleans.

## Import direction examples

```dart
// GOOD: presentation -> domain
import '../../domain/repositories/medication_repository.dart';

// GOOD: data -> domain
import '../../domain/entities/medication.dart';

// BAD: domain -> data
import '../../data/repositories/firebase_medication_repository.dart';
```
